Commit:     Alex Hsu <alex.hsu@advantech.com>
CommitDate: Wed Jun 17 16:53:08 2026 +0800

    feat(mic-741): customize AT7A1 board for JetPack 7.2
    
    Apply MIC-741 AT7A1 board customizations on the JP7.2 (L4T r39.2.0) base.
    
    Device tree / bootloader:
    - bpmp: enable pcie@3, adjust clocks / system-cfg
    - pinmux & gpio BCT: AT7A1 board pin configuration
    - tegra264 / p4071 DT: SPI controllers, PCIe, power LED, gpio-mode
    - nvme.conf, t264.conf.common: driver config
    
    Kernel:
    - defconfig: SPI and related options
    - spi-tegra114: downstream driver (tap-delay / high-speed support)
    - aquantia PHY: driver adjustments
    - conftest (nvidia-oot + unifiedgpudisp): robust compiler-version parsing
    - drop pinctrl-tegra debug override (revert to stock)
    
    Rootfs:
    - nv-oobe.sh: skip OOBE and resize rootfs to full disk on first boot
    - dpkg status: hold nvidia-l4t-kernel / nvidia-l4t-kernel-dtbs ... etc.

